ay.net/images/1790/1790733.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn2.ettoday.net%2Fimages%2F1790%2F1790733.jpg&h=115a4b85&s={SIZE}\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:47:33.000Z","msg":"都似V喎"},{"pid":"31d6bbe25b99011339dfef268811fdb81142cc5f","tid":1968474,"uid":25260,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:49:24.000Z","msg":"Vnivercity <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"663cdc843d2983cf899180dd6b5982b85ef63adc","tid":1968474,"uid":12146,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:50:15.000Z","msg":"Single v single u"},{"pid":"2b1ba70d5f353d474fbac482e77958e51217dc76","tid":1968474,"uid":101481,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:52:42.000Z","msg":"v will v will rock u"},{"pid":"bf53d3da845c31a27da3a01680b8b580d4f55d7b","tid":1968474,"uid":250278,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"b4e06a2a72eea229dfa4715022319da656f1a7ab","tid":1968474,"uid":38518,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:46:16.000Z","msg":"以前U係寫V，例如Bvlgari其實係Bulgari，歷史建築都會見到"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:52:53.000Z","msg":"正解<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n正如kongu東閘成日鬧鬼嗰個The Vniversity of Hong Kong<br />\n係跟返古羅馬拼法 將個U變V<br />\n而唔係D咩鬧鬼<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"46d5dd89ef98450fec00a7fab9b976c4a6f5f3ea","tid":1968474,"uid":62532,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:53:54.000Z","msg":"我Kong V畢業都唔知點解"},{"pid":"6ca20d8420c3ec88990c023f9b57163922642822","tid":1968474,"uid":343161,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:55:08.000Z","msg":"In other Germanic languages, including German (but not Dutch, in which it is pronounced w&eacute;), its name is similar to that of English V. In many languages, its name literally means &quot;double v&quot;: Portuguese duplo v&ecirc;,[note 3] Spanish doble ve (though it can be spelled uve doble),[19][note 4] French double v&eacute;, Icelandic tv&ouml;falt vaff, Czech dvojit&eacute; v&eacute;, Finnish kaksois-vee, etc."},{"pid":"31d479537b1e4709871aea69f5d30e7d0c636683","tid":1968474,"uid":281775,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:55:47.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.grammarphobia.com/blog/2011/04/double-u.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grammarphobia.com%2Fblog%2F2011%2F04%2Fdouble-u.html&d=pQk%2FYDfxyk1It%2BdH9Wj1W1EyhmTkDJ%2BTCVbHNRNdZc8%3D&h=e2580663\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.grammarphobia.com/blog/2011/04/double-u.html</a><br />\nWhy isn&rsquo;t a W called a double v?<br />\nApril 27, 2011<br />\nQ: Why is the letter W called &ldquo;double u&rdquo;? It looks like a &ldquo;double v&rdquo; to me.<br />\n<br />\nA: The name of the 23rd letter of the English alphabet is &ldquo;double u&rdquo; because it was originally written that way in Anglo-Saxon times.<br />\n<br />\nAs the Oxford English Dictionary explains it, the ancient Roman alphabet did not have a letter &ldquo;w.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nSo in the 7th century, when Latin was first used in early Old English writing, it was necessary to invent a symbol to represent that sound.<br />\n<br />\nAt first, the sound was represented by &ldquo;uu&rdquo;&mdash;literally a double &ldquo;u.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nIt wasn&rsquo;t written as a &ldquo;v&rdquo; because the letter &ldquo;v&rdquo; didn&rsquo;t exist in Old English, as we&rsquo;ve written before on the blog. And a double &ldquo;v&rdquo; would not have approximated the sound anyway.<br />\n<br />\nThe &ldquo;uu&rdquo; was replaced by another symbol in the 8th century, a character from the Runic alphabet called a &ldquo;wyn.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nIn the 11th century, the old &ldquo;uu&rdquo; form was reintroduced by Norman scribes in a ligatured (that is, joined) form, written as &ldquo;w.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nBut as the OED says, &ldquo;It has never lost its original name of &lsquo;double U.&rsquo; &rdquo;"},{"pid":"bf7cb94e585fe5522aa98017544e8809151bc1fe","tid":1968474,"uid":4672,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:56:34.000Z","msg":"得b u<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/angel.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"09f29871657eaadc87c43b01bf8fb9756c6a13e8","tid":1968474,"uid":133525,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:56:53.000Z","msg":"吾你老母 死垃圾"},{"pid":"42edd463a3d1228beaebbc584bd01ab4dce02e7b","tid":1968474,"uid":252158,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"09f29871657eaadc87c43b01bf8fb9756c6a13e8","tid":1968474,"uid":133525,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:56:53.000Z","msg":"吾你老母 死垃圾"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:58:04.000Z","msg":"Sor, 唔"},{"pid":"317eb84518f475c1d686ff6b2bab8e6edeea37c0","tid":1968474,"uid":43015,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T17:04:44.000Z","msg":"法文係叫double v&eacute;<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=golDmUTCx_A\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DgolDmUTCx_A&d=pQk%2FYDfxyk1It%2BdH9Wj1W1EyhmTkDJ%2BTCVbHNRNdZc8%3D&h=708a00e2\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=golDmUTCx_A</a>"},{"pid":"5bd5f5b50d1c735c4ad42c57bcf82f78e36624cf","tid":1968474,"uid":336046,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T17:08:09.000Z","msg":"文字都有accent<br />\n東方人字跡較尖棱<br />\n西方較圓潤"},{"pid":"3918ece634fabb59e9dbec2aed9e686cdfd5ba17","tid":1968474,"uid":81309,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"31d479537b1e4709871aea69f5d30e7d0c636683","tid":1968474,"uid":281775,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T16:55:47.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.grammarphobia.com/blog/2011/04/double-u.html\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grammarphobia.com%2Fblog%2F2011%2F04%2Fdouble-u.html&d=pQk%2FYDfxyk1It%2BdH9Wj1W1EyhmTkDJ%2BTCVbHNRNdZc8%3D&h=e2580663\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.grammarphobia.com/blog/2011/04/double-u.html</a><br />\nWhy isn&rsquo;t a W called a double v?<br />\nApril 27, 2011<br />\nQ: Why is the letter W called &ldquo;double u&rdquo;? It looks like a &ldquo;double v&rdquo; to me.<br />\n<br />\nA: The name of the 23rd letter of the English alphabet is &ldquo;double u&rdquo; because it was originally written that way in Anglo-Saxon times.<br />\n<br />\nAs the Oxford English Dictionary explains it, the ancient Roman alphabet did not have a letter &ldquo;w.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nSo in the 7th century, when Latin was first used in early Old English writing, it was necessary to invent a symbol to represent that sound.<br />\n<br />\nAt first, the sound was represented by &ldquo;uu&rdquo;&mdash;literally a double &ldquo;u.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nIt wasn&rsquo;t written as a &ldquo;v&rdquo; because the letter &ldquo;v&rdquo; didn&rsquo;t exist in Old English, as we&rsquo;ve written before on the blog. And a double &ldquo;v&rdquo; would not have approximated the sound anyway.<br />\n<br />\nThe &ldquo;uu&rdquo; was replaced by another symbol in the 8th century, a character from the Runic alphabet called a &ldquo;wyn.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nIn the 11th century, the old &ldquo;uu&rdquo; form was reintroduced by Norman scribes in a ligatured (that is, joined) form, written as &ldquo;w.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nBut as the OED says, &ldquo;It has never lost its original name of &lsquo;double U.&rsquo; &rdquo;"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-04-11T17:15:22.000Z","msg":"又真係無 V 啵<br />\n<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/AVUT4UG.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FAVUT4UG.jpg&h=365d24c6&s={SIZE}\" /> (from wiki)"}]}